{"parentUuid":"90be2c57-b439-45d7-b4f9-319e33cb4324","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"fc70cb2b-4c30-4e29-89ad-937c0f162414","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a44e191e5500aad24","slug":"keen-watching-pony","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Tf6YArA8KeQ9as7uQ3nSSn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 819\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/819](https://www.erdosproblems.com/819)\n    23→\n    24→Let $f(N)$ be maximal such that there exists $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ with\n    25→$|A|=\\lfloor N^{1/2}\\rfloor$ such that $|(A+A)\\cap [1,N]|=f(N)$. Estimate $f(N)$.\n    26→\n    27→Erdős and Freud [ErFr91] proved\n    28→$(3/8-o(1))N \\leq f(N) \\leq (1/2+o(1))N$,\n    29→and note that it is closely connected to the size of the largest quasi-Sidon set\n    30→(see [840]).\n    31→\n    32→[ErFr91] Erdős, P. and Freud, R.\n    33→-/\n    34→\n    35→open Finset\n    36→\n    37→open scoped Pointwise\n    38→\n    39→namespace Erdos819\n    40→\n    41→/-- The maximum of $|(A + A) \\cap \\{1, \\ldots, N\\}|$ over all $A \\subseteq \\{1, \\ldots, N\\}$ with\n    42→$|A| = \\lfloor\\sqrt{N}\\rfloor$. -/\n    43→noncomputable def f (N : ℕ) : ℕ :=\n    44→  ((Finset.Icc 1 N).powerset.filter (fun A => A.card = Nat.sqrt N)).sup\n    45→    (fun A => ((A + A) ∩ Finset.Icc 1 N).card)\n    46→\n    47→/--\n    48→**Erdős Problem 819** — Lower bound (Erdős–Freud [ErFr91]):\n    49→\n    50→For every $\\varepsilon > 0$, for sufficiently large $N$,\n    51→$f(N) \\geq (3/8 - \\varepsilon) N$.\n    52→-/\n    53→@[category research solved, AMS 5]\n    54→theorem erdos_819 :\n    55→    ∀ ε : ℝ, ε > 0 →\n    56→    ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ N : ℕ, N ≥ N₀ →\n    57→    (↑(f N) : ℝ) ≥ (3 / 8 - ε) * (↑N : ℝ) := by\n    58→  sorry\n    59→\n    60→/--\n    61→**Erdős Problem 819** — Upper bound (Erdős–Freud [ErFr91]):\n    62→\n    63→For every $\\varepsilon > 0$, for sufficiently large $N$,\n    64→$f(N) \\leq (1/2 + \\varepsilon) N$.\n    65→-/\n    66→@[category research solved, AMS 5]\n    67→theorem erdos_819.variants.upper_bound :\n    68→    ∀ ε : ℝ, ε > 0 →\n    69→    ∃ N₀ : ℕ, ∀ N : ℕ, N ≥ N₀ →\n    70→    (↑(f N) : ℝ) ≤ (1 / 2 + ε) * (↑N : ℝ) := by\n    71→  sorry\n    72→\n    73→end Erdos819\n    74→"}]},"uuid":"4f09e2f2-8923-4d8c-9cc6-684076731544","timestamp":"2026-03-11T02:49:46.838Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"90be2c57-b439-45d7-b4f9-319e33cb4324"}
